    overviewTitle: 'Project Overview',
    overviewBody: 'Pakistan Data Management Services is pleased to announce the release of an OpenType font for writing Holy Quran text based on the Unicode standard. The font features high quality glyphs and support for all aeraabs and mark placements at proper positions. All waqfs used to identify different pauses in reading are also provided. PDMS Saleem Quran Font provides advanced Arabic typography close to calligraphy while retaining the beauty and legibility of Quran Majeed Arabic text.',
    craftTitle: 'Calligraphy Rooted in Quranic Tradition',
    craftBody: 'The font is developed according to the rules used in Quranic calligraphy in Pakistan, following the style of Yameen Dehlvi, one of the finest Quran calligraphers in Pakistan. Guidance and calligraphy of basic glyphs for the font have been provided by Mr. Mohammed Saleem, who is inspired by the work of Shafiq-uz-Zaman and frequently consults him for guidance.',
    featuresTitle: 'Font Features',
    features: [
      'Unicode-based OpenType support',
      'High quality glyph rendering',
      'Proper aeraab and mark placement',
      'Waqf symbols for reading pauses',
      'Quranic calligraphy-inspired style',
      'Readable yet close to hand-crafted script'
    ],
    typographyTitle: 'Advanced Arabic Typography',
    typographyBody: 'The font is designed to satisfy the needs of Arabic users, designers, and publishers who need Quranic text quality without the technological limitations of older Quran printing methods.',
    typographyChips: ['Unicode standard', 'OpenType font', 'Quran text', 'Arabic calligraphy', 'Publishing ready'],
    aboutTitle: 'About PDMS',
    aboutBody: 'Based in Karachi, Pakistan, PDMS has been developing Urdu software products since 1986. The nationally acclaimed Nastaleeq Nizami Urdu desktop publishing software boosted the use of computers in Pakistan by making them write beautifully in Nastaleeq script. Other products include Urdu Computer Nizam, Ruqqa-UrduEmail, Urdu 98, Urdu Mahir, PDMS Jauhar, and Quran Majeed CD. PDMS has also developed fonts for regional languages like Sindhi and Pushto and designed Urdu portals including UrduSeek.com, UrduNews.net, and CityIslam.com.',
    impactTitle: 'Why This Font Matters',
    impactBody: 'This release gives Arabic users a high quality Quran font built for both spiritual reading and modern digital publishing. It reflects PDMS’s long standing expertise in Arabic and Urdu typography and its commitment to technology that respects the sacred text while improving usability for publishers and designers.',
